metadata.name: Cat 1/20
metadata.description:
As I got ready for bed late at night after a long day of work
So too you would come to bed and arch your back
The happiest part of my day

Your eyes narrowed sleepily and 
A gentle purr as you kneaded the fluffy covers
And everything was right in my world

If I was lucky, you would let me pet you 
Or if I felt fiercely unsatisfied that night
By your independent space, your aloofness
I would pull you to me and bury my face in your soft fur
Nose tickling
As I breathed in your scent with unquenchable love
